{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Compression techniques have become popular to store large-scale point cloud maps (Golla and Klein 2015; Huang and Liu 2019; Wiesmann et al. 2021).",
    "To address the problem of place recognition in a compressed point cloud map, Wiesmann et al. (2022) presented Retriever, a novel deep neural network architecture that directly operates on compressed feature representation, then uses a NetVLAD (Arandjelovic et al. 2016) layer to aggregate local features with an attention mechanism between local features and a latent code.",
    "In summary, feature-based methods are the most common methods in 3D-PCPR.",
    "Their main idea is to directly use hand-crafted or deep learning-based methods on 3D point clouds to extract local or global features, then similarity matching is performed on the extracted point cloud query features and 3D reference map features, and finally achieve the task of subsequent place recognition.",
    "The hand-crafted place recognition methods have good interpretability and high computational efficiency."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Compression techniques have become popular to store large-scale point cloud maps (Golla and Klein 2015; Huang and Liu 2019; Wiesmann et al. 2021).",
